---
name: signal-id-bridged
backends: [int, v2]
---

# std/ui signal(name, default).id resolves on the bridged v2 lane

Regression for `v2-bridged-ui-signal-id-field`: on `run --v2` (FrontendBridge), a
std/ui `signal` bridged from the v1 plugin as a NamedMethodObj exposed `.set` but not
`.id`, crashing `__method__: no field 'id'`. The bridged ReactiveSignal now exposes its
`id` (its stable name) like the native ui-plugin's NativeUiSignal.

```scalascript
val s = signal("myid", "before")
s.set("after")
println(s.id)
```
